<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900413-0159</DOCNO><DOCID>900413-0159.</DOCID><HL>   Hong Kong's Payroll Costs</HL><DATE>04/13/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   FREST</CO><LP>   HONG KONG -- The government said payroll expenses faroutstripped inflation in December, providing fresh evidenceof Hong Kong's wage spiral.   Monthly wages in the manufacturing sector, the colony'slargest, climbed 16% in December from a year earlier, or 5.3%after accounting for inflation. The increase was even moremarked in the trading, restaurant and hotels field, climbing17%, or 6.2% in real terms. Payroll costs in the financialservices sector lagged behind, rising 13% in nominal termsand 3% after inflation.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>